(c)  forty percent (40%) of the assumed monthly wages for the third and
fourth months;
(d)  thirty percent (30%) of the assumed monthly wages for the fifth and
sixth months.

3.  The rates for the reduced income allowance shall be as follows:
(a)  eighty percent (80%) of the assumed monthly wages for the first
month;
(b)  fifty percent (50%) of the assumed monthly wages for the second
month;
(c)  forty percent (40%) of the assumed monthly wages for the third and
fourth months;
(d)  thirty percent (30%) of the assumed monthly wages for the fifth and
sixth months.
